            <note xml:id="n06082702" n="2">Here <name type="person" key="Clark, William">Clark</name> gets a good view of the <name type="place" key="Niobrara Formation">Niobrara Formation</name>, an impure chalk or marl, which later became famous for the fossil skeletons of marine reptiles and remains of foraminifera (one-celled animals) which it contains in abundance. The glassy substance is probably the coating of a concretion or nodule which is common in the <name type="place" key="Niobrara Formation">Niobrara</name>. <name type="person" key="Clark, William">Clark's</name> references to cobalt and ore are wishful thinking as no metallic ores have been discovered here.</note>
